Serves 4
There are 4 parts to this: cucumber, tofu, sauce, greens
Serve it on rice
/////
Lightly pickled chilli cucumber:
    Cut in half and then slice:
          2 lebanese cucumbers
    Add the following:
          2 tablespoons soy sauce
          2 tablespoons rice wine vinegar
          2 tablespoons crunchy chilli oil
    Set aside
/////
Tofu:
    Dry and then slice into 2cm cubes:
          400-500g packet tofu
    In a bowl add:
          A drizzle of soy to coat
    Leave to marinade for a bit while making the sauce
    Just before frying, sprinkle with:
          A couple of teaspoons of cornflour 
    Fry in hot pan till each side is crispy
/////
Sauce:
    Mix well together:
          Half a cup ground peanuts (or peanut butter)
          2 cloves garlic, minced
          About a tablespoon finely grated ginger
          1 tablespoon sesame oil
          1 tablespoon rice wine vinegar
          2 tablespoons soy sauce
          1 tablespoon maple syrup
          1 teaspoon Chinese all spice 
          About 4 tablespoons hot water
    Add sauce to fried tofu and allow to mix through quickly
/////
Warm crunchy greens:
    Make a dressing of:
          Juice of half a lemon
          1 teaspoon wasabi paste
          1 teaspoon maple syrup
    Slice:
          Broccoli
          Sugar snap peas
          Snow peas
    Add to a hot pan with a little oil, fry till just softened and a bit charred
    Mix with dressing
/////
Bringing it together:
  Rice + peanut tofu + lightly pickled chilli cucumber + warm crunchy greens
